D\n\nSet soft story targets\n\nStory setup preferences will hold the planning targets that guide pacing and length without turning them into hard constraints.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\n\nThe route is previewing story setup via the stage query parameter while the durable session state remains at composition.\n\nCurrent setup\n\n~14 minutes, 1800 words, 4 chapters, about 10 scenes\n\nKeep each chapter ending calmer than it began.\n\nRevision 1\nSaved Apr 2, 8:43 AM\n\nExpectation setting\n\nGuides, not guarantees\n\nThese numbers help the planner balance pacing, chapter shape, and read-aloud feel. They are honest suggestions, not hard guarantees.\n\nSoft targets\nBedtime-first\n\nNext step\n\nComposition can use this plan\n\nComposition, Audio, Finalize may need another pass after these targets change.\n\nPreview composition\nEdits refresh later production work\n\nUpdating these targets creates a fresh saved revision. Composition, audio, and finalize may need another pass afterward, because they treat these as planning input.\n\nPlanning targets\n\nSet the rough length and structure you want the writing stage to aim for. The planner will treat these as nearby targets, not strict requirements.\n\nUnsaved edits\nTarget word count\n\nA soft word target helps later composition estimate density and pacing without forcing an exact final count.\n\nTarget word count should stay between 100 and 10000.\n\nTarget read-aloud duration (minutes)\n\nUse the read-aloud duration you would like to land near. The written story may be a little shorter or longer.\n\nChapter count\n\nChapter count sets the broad pacing shape for the reading experience.\n\nApproximate scene count\n\nScene count is optional. Use it when you want a rough sense of how many distinct story turns the plan should hold.\n\nPacing notes\n\nUse this for pacing or structural guidance that does not fit neatly into a number, such as 'keep each chapter ending calmer than it began.'\n\nSave story setup\nReset\nReview beat sheet\n\nSaved Apr 2, 8:43 AM\n\nPlanner summary\n\n~14 minutes, 4 chapters, about 10 scenes\n\nThis rail shows the current pacing plan the backend will carry into composition prompts and later runtime estimates.\n\nUnsaved changes\nSTORY LANE\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\nBEAT SHEET\nRevision 1\nSAVED STATE\nSaved Apr 2, 8:43 AM\nWord count and runtime\n\n14 minutes usually lands near 2000 words, often somewhere around 1700-2200.\n\nChapter sizing\n\nAt a calm pace, 14 minutes across 4 chapters often means about 500 words per chapter. That works out to about 2.5 scenes per chapter.\n\nAssumptions\n\nRead-aloud estimates assume about 140 words per minute, with most bedtime narration landing between 120 and 160. Chapter sizing assumes individual chapters can drift by about 15% around the average rather than matching perfectly.\n\nProgress\n\nWorkflow progress\n7 of 10 stages complete\n\nResume at Composition with 70% of the workflow currently complete.\n\nStory lane\n\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\n\nA child and an otter guardian guide the harbor lanterns home before bed.\n\nProduction\n\nComposition\n\n~14 minute runtime / 1800 words / 4 chapters / about 10 scenes\n    at assertText (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:66:11)\n    at async runStep (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:137:7)\n    at async main (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:224:7)\n\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"mkdir -p .artifacts/webapp-qa && cat > .artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-51-story-setup-heuristics.spec.json <<'EOF'\n{\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://frontend:8566/sessions/8155bbd7-2de7-4d4c-a961-d35485225ed0?stage=story_setup\\\",\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-51-story-setup-heuristics.png\\\",\n  \\\"viewport\\\": { \\\"width\\\": 1440, \\\"height\\\": 1200 },\n  \\\"timeout\\\": 20000,\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForText\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Planning targets\\\" },\n    