\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nNeeds refresh\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nSet soft story targets\n\nStory setup preferences will hold the planning targets that guide pacing and length without turning them into hard constraints.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\n\nThe route is previewing story setup via the stage query parameter while the durable session state remains at composition.\n\nCurrent setup\n\n~14 minutes, 1800 words, 4 chapters, about 10 scenes\n\nKeep each chapter ending calmer than it began.\n\nRevision 1\nSaved Apr 2, 8:43 AM\n\nExpectation setting\n\nGuides, not guarantees\n\nThese numbers help the planner balance pacing, chapter shape, and read-aloud feel. They are honest suggestions, not hard guarantees.\n\nSoft targets\nBedtime-first\n\nNext step\n\nComposition can use this plan\n\nComposition, Audio, Finalize may need another pass after these targets change.\n\nPreview composition\nEdits refresh later production work\nUpdating these targets creates a fresh saved revision. Composition, audio, and finalize may need another pass afterward, because they treat these as planning input.\nPlanning targets\n\nSet the rough length and structure you want the writing stage to aim for. The planner will treat these as nearby targets, not strict requirements.\n\nSaved\nTarget word count\n\nA soft word target helps later composition estimate density and pacing without forcing an exact final count.\n\nTarget read-aloud duration (minutes)\n\nUse the read-aloud duration you would like to land near. The written story may be a little shorter or longer.\n\nChapter count\n\nChapter count sets the broad pacing shape for the reading experience.\n\nApproximate scene count\n\nScene count is optional. Use it when you want a rough sense of how many distinct story turns the plan should hold.\n\nPacing notes\n\nUse this for pacing or structural guidance that does not fit neatly into a number, such as 'keep each chapter ending calmer than it began.'\n\nSave story setup\nReset\nReview beat sheet\n\nSaved Apr 2, 8:43 AM\n\nPlanner summary\n\n~14 minutes, 1800 words, 4 chapters, about 10 scenes\n\nThis rail shows the current pacing plan the backend will carry into composition prompts and later runtime estimates.\n\nSaved\nSTORY LANE\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\nBEAT SHEET\nRevision 1\nSAVED STATE\nSaved Apr 2, 8:43 AM\nWord count and runtime\n\n1800 words in 14 minutes implies about 129 words per minute, which stays inside the usual bedtime range.\n\nChapter sizing\n\n4 chapters at 1800 words usually lands near 450 words per chapter, often roughly 400-500. That works out to about 2.5 scenes per chapter.\n\nAssumptions\n\nRead-aloud estimates assume about 140 words per minute, with most bedtime narration landing between 120 and 160. Chapter sizing assumes individual chapters can drift by about 15% around the average rather than matching perfectly.\n\nProgress\n\nWorkflow progress\n7 of 10 stages complete\n\nResume at Composition with 70% of the workflow currently complete.\n\nStory lane\n\nQuest Fantasy / Hushed Wonder\n\nA child and an otter guardian guide the harbor lanterns home before bed.\n\nProduction\n\nComposition\n\n~14 minute runtime / 1800 words / 4 chapters / about 10 scenes\n    at assertText (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:66:11)\n    at async runStep (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:137:7)\n    at async main (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:224:7)\n\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"cat > .artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-51-story-setup-heuristics.spec.json <<'EOF'\n{\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://frontend:8566/sessions/8155bbd7-2de7-4d4c-a961-d35485225ed0?stage=story_setup\\\",\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-51-story-setup-heuristics.png\\\",\n  \\\"viewport\\\": { \\\"width\\\": 1440, \\\"height\\\": 1200 },\n  \\\"timeout\\\": 20000,\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForText\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Planning targets\\\" },\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Composition can use this plan\\\" },\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"14 minutes usually lands near 2000 words, often somewhere around 1700-2200.\\\" },\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"At a calm pace, 14 minutes across 4 chapters often means about 500 words per chapter. That works out to about 2.5 scenes per chapter.\\\" },\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Read-aloud estimates assume about 140 words per minute, with most bedtime narration landing between 120 and 160. Chapter sizing assumes individual chapters can drift by about 15% around the average rather than matching perfectly.\\\" },\n    { \\\"action\\\": \\\"screenshot\\\", \\\"fullPage\\\": true }\n  ]\n}\nEOF\n\ndocker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-51-story-setup-heuristics.spec.json\"", "exit_code": 1, "id": "item_112", "status": "failed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 227, "prompt_index": 52, "prompt_name": "51 \u2014 Correlation Heuristics for Word Count, Runtime, and Chapters", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T02:11:20-07:00"}
